Brazil Stocks to Recover as CPI Peaks in Quarter, JPMorgan Says

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-07-08T14:08:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/brazil-stocks-to-recover-as-cpi-peaks-in-quarter-jpmorgan-says.html
Brazilian stocks will likely recover
as interest-rate increases and inflation peak this quarter,
JPMorgan Chase & Co. said.  JPMorgan is “especially bullish” on banks such as  Itau
Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4)  and  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4) , and homebuilders
including PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes and MRV
Engenharia & Participacoes SA, analyst Emy Shayo Cherman wrote
in a report e-mailed to clients today.  “There is more macro visibility than at any time in the
past year,” Shayo wrote.  The benchmark Bovespa index is down 11 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  